  "market_context": "Weekly profile where Monday formed a reversal (not expansion), Tuesday–Wednesday expanded upward, Thursday countered the range downward, and Friday continued toward the weekly open despite the imperfect pattern.",
  "key_observation": "The analyst emphasized that even when Monday does not expand (only reverses), the Thursday counter logic still holds and can lead to a valid Friday continuation toward the weekly open.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify the weekly structure: Monday formed a reversal candle, not an expansion.",
    "Step 2: Observe Tuesday and Wednesday as consecutive expansion days (upward move).",
    "Step 3: Note Thursday’s counter move lower, violating the ideal 'Mon-Tue-Wed expansion' requirement but still acting as a range counter.",
    "Step 4: Confirm Friday’s continuation move toward the weekly open, validating the underlying logic despite the imperfect setup."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "The core logic of the Thursday counter weekly profile remains applicable even with deviations (e.g., Monday reversal instead of expansion); structural intent matters more than rigid pattern adherence.",
